'''''The State of the World's Children''''' is an annual report published by the [[United Nations Children's Emergency Fund]] (UNICEF). It is the flagship publication of the organization.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.unicef.org/sowc/ |title=The State of the World's Children reports}}</ref> The first report was published in 1980, having been introduced by [[James P. Grant]] (the executive director of UNICEF at the time).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.unicef.org/about/history/index_sowc.html |title=State of the World's Children (1980-1995)}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1995/01/30/obituaries/james-p-grant-unicef-chief-and-aid-expert-is-dead-at-72.html |author=Barbara Crossette |date=January 30, 1995 |title=James P. Grant, Unicef Chief And Aid Expert, Is Dead at 72}}</ref> Peter Adamson was the author of the report for 15 years.<ref name="jim_grant_book">{{cite book |title=Jim Grant: UNICEF Visionary |author=Peter Adamson, Carol Bellamy, Kul Gautam, Richard Jolly, Nyi Nyi, Mary Racelis, Richard Reid, Jon Rohde |year=2001 |url=http://www.unicef.org/publications/index_4402.html |publisher=UNICEF Innocenti Research Centre}}</ref> The publication of the 1982–1983 ''The State of the World's Children'' report marked the start of the [[child survival revolution]].<ref name="fifield">{{cite book |title=A Mighty Purpose: How Jim Grant Sold the World on Saving Its Children |year= 2015 |publisher=Other Press|first=Adam |last=Fifield}}</ref>{{rp|95}}

Following the end of Grant's tenure at UNICEF and his death in 1995, ''The State of the World's Children'' has received significantly less attention.<ref name=fifield/>{{rp|390}}

The 2015 ''The State of the World's Children'' report reviewed the work on children's health in the world in the context of the 25th anniversary of the [[Convention on the Rights of the Child]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.unicef.org/publications/files/SOWC_2015_Summary_and_Tables.pdf |title=THE STATE OF THE WORLD’S CHILDREN 2015: Executive Summary |publisher=UNICEF}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crop.org/OtherResources/FurtherReading/UNICEF-The-State-of-the-Worlds-Children-in-Numbers-.aspx |title=UNICEF: The State of the World’s Children in Numbers |date=August 24, 2015 |accessdate=May 4, 2016}}</ref>

